text:
Fort Greene Place, east side (extreme right), south from Fulton Street, showing debris after a row of buildings both on Fort Green Place and Fulton Street were razed and the area later cleared for a used car sales lot. In the background is the rear of the Y.M.C.A. Building which
fronts on Hanson Place.
July 5, 1930
P. L. Sperr
(2)
South on the east side of Fort Greene Place from Fulton Street, ten years later. Note the used car sales
lot.
July 5, 1930
P. L. Sperr
title: Brooklyn: Fort Hamilton - 59th Street

text:
59th Street, north side, just east of Fort Hamilton Parkway, showing Public School No. 105.
Board of Education of the City of New York Early 1930's
title: Public Schools - Brooklyn - P.S. 105.
